{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e6ada75b-5713-4f12-afaa-53ee2edd644a","content":"With xUnit v3 on MTP, `dotnet test --filter` uses the **MTP filter expression syntax**, which differs from the old VSTest syntax:\n\n| Concept | VSTest (v2) | MTP (v3) |\n|---------|-------------|----------|\n| Contains | `~` | `~` |\n| AND | `&` | `&` |\n| Trait | `Category=Smoke` | `Category=Smoke` |\n\nThe operators are actually the same here — **but** MTP requires the `--filter` value to be passed with `--` separator when invoking via `dotnet test`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nThe key change: with `<UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>`, arguments after `--` are forwarded to the MTP test host. Without `--`, `dotnet test --filter` may not reach the MTP runner correctly.\n\nAlternatively, you can run the test executable directly (xUnit v3 projects produce an executable):\n\n```bash\ndotnet run -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n**Summary:** The filter expression itself is compatible — the difference is *how you pass it*. Use `dotnet test -- --filter \"<expr>\"` (note the `--` separator).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"50c3b45f-d1fa-4dd5-8084-f24bd911b7d5","outputTokens":338,"requestId":"BC52:1CADF2:1B9EB21:1EB8258:69FA9115"},"id":"43236d51-cab5-4fff-b8b1-3ebddb18de74","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:53:50.170Z","parentId":"8f6481ba-ed8b-4093-b0f0-3ddba497a80d"}
